description.narrative:
The project aims to influence decision-makers at regional and national level through advocacy actions to increase budgetary allocations in the education, health, agriculture and water and sanitation sectors.
The main results targeted by the project are:
-Implementation of Budget citizen control spaces;
-Capacity building of CSOs in citizen monitoring of the budget;
- Advocacy at the local and national levels for increased budgets for education, health and agriculture.
To achieve these results, the following activities will be carried out:
-Conducting a baseline study
-Establishment of a citizen budget monitoring committee.
-Conduct summary analyzes of budget allocations for the education, health and agriculture sectors
-Organize three mini-conferences on budget monitoring and advocacy for CSO platforms.
-Implementing budgetary advocacy in areas of intervention at national level.
The project will be implemented in the&nbsp;03 regions of Burkina Faso and at national level.The target groups are the national and local authorities. The beneficiaries are the local populations.
